<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1718">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850d.00/328.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Conference adjourned this morning to meet again in February next. No acts
                            were signed. Nielsen will obtain passage for America at the earliest
                            possible date. Adee leaves tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>